Chicken Zucchini Enchilada Casserole

Sauce:
24 oz tomato sauce (strained or crushed tomatoes)
2 tsp taco seasoning
1 tsp cumin
1 tsp garlic powder
1/2 tsp salt
1/4 tsp ground black pepper

In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients and set aside.

Filling:
1 1/2 lbs chicken thighs or breasts, boneless & skinless
1/2 tsp taco seasoning
1/2 tsp cumin
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1/2 tsp salt

In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients, mix with your hands and let marinate for 5-10 min. Preheat large skillet on medium heat and add chicken. Cover and cook for 10-12 min, turning once. Let cool a bit, transfer to a cutting board and shred.

Casserole:
3 large zucchini, cut lengthwise into 1/8" thick slices
3 tbsp quinoa, uncooked & divided
1 1/2 c (6oz) mozzarella/cheddar/pepper jack cheese, shredded
1 jalapeno pepper, seeded and diced

Preheat oven to 375F. In a medium 8x11" baking dish add a few tbsp of sauce, spread to coat and sprinkle with 1 tbsp of quinoa. Place sliced zucchini widthwise overlapping a bit to create a single layer. Spread half the chicken, then half the sauce, top with cheese and jalapenos, and sprinkle with 1 tbsp quinoa. Repeat another layer, finishing with a layre of zucchini and sprinkly cheese on top. Bake covered tightly for 45 min, then uncovered for another 20 min and broil on high for 5 min or until cheese has browned. Let stand for 10 min before slicing. Can store in airtight container in refrigerator for up to 5 days.
